{"key":"processedPost-6654987","value":{"id":6654987,"first":6654971,"last":6656364,"when":1173529204,"utime":"03/10/07 02:20 PM","content":"Those ratios should work fine.  Toss in that mornings coffee grinds if you have them as well.  If the mix seems a bit 'heavy' you can throw in ten percent or so of vermiculite to break it up.<br /><br />If you leave manure soaking too long, bacteria will bloom and it will stink up your place.<br /><br />You rarely have to pH balance a substrate such as yours.  Mycelium actually prefers a slightly acidic substrate anyway, and the gypsum will bring it up a tad as it is.  Save the calcium carbonate and lime for your casing layer. <br />RR","title":"Re: need guidance for substrate","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}